Bing Hsu is Bing was the youngest of An-mei’s and George Hsu’s seven children. When Bing was four years old, the entire Hsu family took a trip to the beach, and Bing drowned. Rose, rather irrationally, blames herself for the death. An-mei had faith that God and hernengkan,or her belief in her power to control her fate, would help her find Bing, but the boy never turned up.